      <akn:section eId="sec_21_103">
        <akn:num>21-103</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Appointment of guardians of the person by court; limitation of number of wards.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_21-103_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>When an infant has neither a natural nor testamentary guardian, a guardian of the person may be appointed by the Probate Court in its own discretion or on the application of a next friend of the infant.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_21-103_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Only trust companies may act as guardian of the person for more than five infants at one time, unless the infants are members of one family.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
